wdi2-NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD.def: Net forest depletion is calculated as the product of unit resource rents and the excess of roundwood harvest over natural growth. If growth exceeds harvest, this figure is zero.
wdi2-NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD.name: Adjusted savings
wdi2-NY.ADJ.DFOR.CD.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.
